Global Funds Buy Net 15.5 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-06-02T03:23:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/global-funds-buy-net-15-5-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 15.5
billion rupees ($345 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.9 percent to 859.3 billion rupees, or 37
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 4.45 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
